        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 4:34PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 433 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Ayersville, or near Sandy Ridge, moving northwest
at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Eden...
Martinsville...
Wentworth...
Mayodan...
Madison...
Walnut Cove...
and Stoneville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
